            <h1 class="vt-lg text-center text-danger">What is this?</h1>
            <p class="vt-sm">A text-based or tabletop roleplaying game is a set of tools, with which you create your own characters, monsters, dungeons, and stories. The player is in full control of design. The themes, difficulty of gameplay, and risk/reward are all up to the player, with the only limit being your imagination.</p>
            <p class="vt-sm">A selection of heroes, monsters, dungeons, and parties are provided for the purposes of demonstration, upon which you can endlessly expand and fine-tune. You're encouraged to design your own characters and worlds within this framework. Along the way you might find, for example, that some monsters you create are too weak, or too powerful, and solving this is all a part of the game.</p>    
